qas.question: The Presbyterian denominations from the British Isles were inspired by these principles in what document?
When was the Directory of Public Worship developed?
Which government enacted the Directory of Public Worship teachings into law?
Which denomination's heritage can be traced to Westminster Assembly?
Which denomination's heritage can be traced to John Calvin?
Which denomination's heritage can be traced to John Knox?
Which Directory was enacted into law by John Calvin?
Which Directory was enacted into law by Westminster Assembly?

context: <b3_0><b4_0><b5_0>Presbyterian<b5_0/><b4_0/><b3_0/> denominations that trace their heritage to the British Isles usually organise their church services inspired by the principles in the <a0_0><b6_0><b7_0>Directory of Public Worship<b7_0/><b6_0/><a0_0/>, developed by the Westminster Assembly in the <a1_0>1640s<a1_0/>. This directory documented Reformed worship practices and theology adopted and developed over the preceding century by British Puritans, initially guided by John Calvin and John Knox. It was enacted as law by the <a2_0>Scottish Parliament<a2_0/>, and became one of the foundational documents of Presbyterian church legislation elsewhere.
